      void fireEmployees()
      This method reads in from the fire file and removes the employee object that it matches in the file
      void getEmployees()
      Reads in the employees text file, creates new employee objects, and places them into the ObjectList named employee
      void hireEmployees()
      Takes employees from the hire file and places them in order to the employee list
      void numberOfEmployees()
      Prints out the number of employees currently on payroll
      void outputEmployees()
      Runs through employees list and outputs the information of each employee
      void outputEmployeesHeader()
      Header used for formatting when outputting employees
      void raise()
      This method finds employees who are making under a certain amount and gives them a raise then outputs their name with their new salary amount
      void seniorMaking35()
      This method finds people making over 35,000 and have at least 5 years with the company then outputs their names
      void sort()
      Sorts the employee list then outputs the sorted list
      void womenOnPayroll()
      Finds all the women on payroll and prints out their first and last name
